      • getANameForSIF

        public String getANameForSIF(BioPAXElement element)
        This method is used when we want to use readable names in the simple SIF format instead of IDs. Note that those names may not be unique. In that case the file will contain duplicate names. This method iterates fields of the element to find a name.
        Parameters:
        element - element to get a name.
        Returns:
        a name to use in SIF
